docs.abstract: President-elect Donald J. Trump is considering nominees who fit more comfortably within his often erratic worldview, in which deal-making reigns over ideology.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Republican Party used to have a label for the kind of foreign policy hawk that President-elect Donald J. Trump named on Tuesday as his national security adviser and is considering as his secretary of state: neocons.

headline.main: Once They Were Neocons. Now Trump’s Foreign Policy Picks Are All ‘America First.’
headline.print_headline: President-Elect’s Foreign Policy Picks  Align With ‘America First’ Viewpoints

byline.original: By David E. Sanger and Catie Edmondson

docs.abstract: President Biden will attend global summits in Peru and Brazil as world leaders prepare for the return of Donald Trump’s isolationist foreign policy.
docs.snippet: President Biden will attend global summits in Peru and Brazil as world leaders prepare for the return of Donald Trump’s isolationist foreign policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Biden’s trip to Peru and Brazil, which starts Thursday, was supposed to have been his final chance to tell fellow world leaders that he was right all along — former President Donald J. Trump was a one-time aberration whose America First policies had been swept aside by voters.

headline.main: Biden’s Swan Song: A Diplomatic Trip Overshadowed by Trump’s Victory
headline.print_headline: Biden Diplomatic Trip a Swan Song for Him and U.S. Foreign Policy

byline.original: By Michael D. Shear and Zolan Kanno-Youngs

docs.abstract: Foreign leaders have rushed to ingratiate themselves with Donald J. Trump in recent days, nervously recalling the clashes, insults and feuds of his first presidency.
docs.snippet: Foreign leaders have rushed to ingratiate themselves with Donald J. Trump in recent days, nervously recalling the clashes, insults and feuds of his first presidency.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Prime Minister Keir Starmer met Donald J. Trump at Trump Tower for dinner on Sept. 26, it was part of a British charm offensive to nurture a relationship between a left-wing leader and a right-wing potential president. So when Mr. Trump turned to Mr. Starmer before parting and told him, “We are friends,” according to a person involved in the evening, it did not go unnoticed.

headline.main: Smile, Flatter and Barter: How the World Is Prepping for Trump Part II
headline.print_headline: Foreign Chiefs Quicken Stride To Trump’s Ear

byline.original: By Mark Landler, Matina Stevis-Gridneff and Marc Santora

docs.abstract: A two-time Pulitzer Prize winner, he was a reporter, editor and columnist for The Washington Post, renowned for his deeply sourced dispatches.
docs.snippet: A two-time Pulitzer Prize winner, he was a reporter, editor and columnist for The Washington Post, renowned for his deeply sourced dispatches.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jim Hoagland, whose long career as a foreign correspondent, editor and columnist for The Washington Post brought him two Pulitzer Prizes and made his work a must-read among the nation’s top diplomats and politicians, died on Monday in Washington. He was 84.

headline.main: Jim Hoagland, Distinguished Journalist on World Affairs, Dies at 84
headline.print_headline: Jim Hoagland, 84, Foreign Reporter Whose Work Earned Him 2 Pulitzers

docs.abstract: President Biden hosted his final pre-election international visitor in the Oval Office, where the talk focused on the Middle East and Europe. But uncertainty in the United States hung over the meeting.
docs.snippet: President Biden hosted his final pre-election international visitor in the Oval Office, where the talk focused on the Middle East and Europe. But uncertainty in the United States hung over the meeting.
docs.lead_paragraph: Without much attention, President Biden this week hosted his last foreign leader in the Oval Office before Tuesday’s election. They discussed the wars in the Middle East and Europe and plotted ways to work together to defeat aggression and alleviate suffering.

headline.main: As Election Nears, Foreign Leaders Fear ‘a Vacuum’ in American Leadership
headline.print_headline: As Election Day Nears, Foreign Leaders Fear ‘a Vacuum’ in American Leadership

docs.abstract: A second Donald J. Trump presidency would almost certainly mark a return to an era of foreign policy decrees, untethered to any policy process, at a moment of maximum international peril.
docs.snippet: A second Donald J. Trump presidency would almost certainly mark a return to an era of foreign policy decrees, untethered to any policy process, at a moment of maximum international peril.
docs.lead_paragraph: What Donald J. Trump promised in his first term in office was America First. What he delivered, as his allies, adversaries and many of his former aides remember it, was chaotic foreign policymaking.

headline.main: Trump Had an ‘America First’ Foreign Policy. But It Was a Breakdown in American Policymaking.

docs.abstract: The U.N. climate conference, held in a petrostate, is a surreal moment. This darkly funny novel about Baku, oil companies and climate change in the first Trump term helps make sense of it all.
docs.snippet: The U.N. climate conference, held in a petrostate, is a surreal moment. This darkly funny novel about Baku, oil companies and climate change in the first Trump term helps make sense of it all.
docs.lead_paragraph: The irony is extreme: This year’s annual United Nations climate change summit is in Baku, Azerbaijan, the petrostate where the modern oil industry was born.

headline.main: The Perfect Novel for the Baku Climate Summit

docs.abstract: The return to power of President-elect Donald J. Trump, who has vowed to confront China on tariffs, has created deep uncertainty about the U.S. role in avoiding global conflicts.
